history.content: Unfortunately 168 is full. Students may get off the waitlist if a student drops from their section, but this will only happen on a one-by-one basis. For example, if you are #1 on the waitlist for your section and a student drops, you will take their place. As all discussions seem to have waitlists of 5+ (note, i didn't double check this), dropping and re-adding the class is unlikely to make a difference. As CS 168 is a phase I class, we would encourage you to make a back-up plan.

If you change sections (by dropping/reenrolling), you will lose your position on the waitlist, yes.

history.content:
I'm number 35 on the waitlist for CS 168 and really hoping to get into the class since this is my last semester!  I was wondering if its a good idea for me to drop the class in order to re-add myself to a class without a discussion waitlist.  I feel like this is a better bet to get into the class but I'm a bit worried because I don't want to lose my place on the waitlist should it not work out.  

I did this with EE 16a and it worked out but they also specifically told me to do this over email so I'm a little more worried about doing that for this one....

Any advice appreciated!

PS - I need one more CS class to graduate this semester and at this point this class is my best chance to get into one (I'm #86 on the waitlist for 161 but that seems even less likely to happen)
